properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: One day heat event continues today. Daytime temperatures near 32 degrees Celsius continue this evening with humidex values near 38. Relief from the heat is expected tonight as a much cooler airmass moves into the area. These conditions pose a health risk when you are not used to the heat. Everyone is at risk from heat, especially older adults; infants and young children; and people with chronic illnesses. You are advised to 1) drink plenty of cool liquids before feeling thirsty; and 2) keep cool by dressing for the weather and spending a few hours each day in a cool place. Hot and humid air can bring deteriorating air quality and can result in the Air Quality Health Index to approach the high risk category. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: High Water Advisory Is Being Issued For Southwestern, Western And Central Regions In Manitoba.
properties.Summary:
Description: This is a Manitoba Emergency Alert. Manitoba Infrastructure’s Hydrologic Forecast Centre has issued a High Water Advisory for southwestern, western and central regions of Manitoba. A weather system may release 75 to 100 millimetres of rain in these areas in between June 28 to July 1. Areas in southwest Manitoba, including Virden and Brandon could see up to 175 millimetres of rain during this time. If you are in the affected area, be watchful as local waterways are expected to rise quickly and may cause flooding. There is a potential for overland flooding in low lying areas. Do not attempt to cross fast flowing waters or waters of unknown depth. Use caution when driving on all roads as road conditions may have changed. Avoid flooded areas. Follow all directions by local authorities, listen for updates and take all necessary precautions to stay safe. Stay tuned to local media for updates.
Expires: 2020-07-02T16:00:00-05:00
Originated from CAP Alert: Manitoba Emergency Measures Organization, 2020-06-28T14:46:14-05:00, E0C254F4-F9A3-0CC2-58B8-5A988B33989E
